<h1>CHAPTER 8 - HISTOLOGICAL METHODS</h1>
<h2>Preparing subbed slides for sections</h2>
(Source: K. Larison) 
<p>For most purposes (e.g. immunohistochemistry and in situ hybridization) Vectabond 
  (Vector Laboratories, 800-227-6666) works well for coating slides. 
</p><p>For epon and paraffin embedded sections, gelatin subbed slides may be more 
  appropriate. To prepare subbed slides:
</p><p>1. Soak new microslides overnight in acid cleaning solution (eg.chromium sulfuric 
  acid.) A strong solution of Micro can be substituted. 
</p><p>2. Wash slides thoroughly in running tap water and rinse in several changes 
  of dH2O. 
</p><p>3. Transfer slides into slide carriers and dip three times in the gelatin solution. 
</p><p>4.Tto avoid streaking, rap the slide carrier vigorously on a paper towel on 
  the counter top following the last immersion. 
</p><p>5. Drain well and dry overnight at 40C.
</p><p>Gelatin subbing solution:
</p><p>0.5% gelatin<br>
  0.05% CrK(SO4)x12H2O.
</p><hr>
